args: Um, Mitsuba? I have a message for you.
It's um... It's from Nanakusa.\nIt's marked 'super-extra-urgent.'
*sigh* Another overbearing letter, huh?\nMy family's a bunch of worrywarts.
I'm fine, but I've gotta run over to\nSeven Leaves. See you later!
Fancy seeing you here during the\nlunch rush, sis. Table for one?
It's bad enough that you've been buying up\nAlberian restaurants by the dozens, but\nnow you want Nanakusa too? Come on!
Finally got word of that, did you?\nYep! That's been my goal all along.
You're telling me you've been trying\nto take over Nanakusa from the start?
Silly me, I could've sworn I said the\nexact words ＂I want to crush Nanakusa.＂
But why, Nazuna?\nDo you hate Nanakusa?\nDo you hate...your family?
What are you talking about, sis?\nI love you all to death. Seriously.
Taking the restaurant down is my way of\nshowing how much I care about my family.
Let me get this straight: Destroying the\neatery that means so much to your family\nis somehow a show of love.
Yup. As things stand now, Nanakusa's\non its way out, regardless of what I do.\nStill clinging to tradition to the end.
Father wouldn't have wanted that. He'd\nwant us to share the Hinomotoan cuisine\nhe so adored with folks around the world.
That's why I started Seven Leaves\nand expanded operations this far.
＂A welcoming atmosphere at an\naffordable price point. Fast, cheap,\ndelicious Hinomotoan cuisine.＂

So by prioritizing efficiency, you can
serve Hinomotoan food to as many
people as possible. That's how you
uphold Nanakusa's legacy?
Yep. It's a new Nanakusa for a new era.\nMy business model is clearly working, too.
After all, I've worked hard enough that\nI can now afford to buy Nanakusa out.
Our brothers and sisters aren't convinced\nyet, but they'll realize I'm right soon.\nThat includes you, Mitsuba.
Surely the girl who left home to create\na flavor that would surpass father's legacy\ncan understand where I'm coming from.
Honestly? I do. Your logic is sound.
But what you're doing now?\nThis isn't the way to succeed Nanakusa.
...And what do you mean by that?
Let me assure you: Even as I've expanded,\nI've NEVER compromised on taste.\nAnd I regard Nanakusa's cuisine highly.
I know that. The food your Seven Leaves\nchef made at L'Amandier was spectacular.
But that's not what I meant. Your way of\ndoing things doesn't carry on Father's soul.

Rrgh... What do you even know? You've
spent who-knows-how-long trying to
surpass his legacy, and what do you have
to show for it? Nothing, that's what!
I know more than you, at least.\nWant me to prove it?
Huh? How are you going to do that?
By cooking, duh. We're chefs.\nLet's compete, Nazuna—for Nanakusa.
We'll find out fair and square who's\nthe worthy successor to Nanakusa.
Fine. You're clearly blinded by your\nfoolish ideals. It's about time I gave\nyou a wake-up call.
We'll have one round. The one who makes\nthe audience coo with delight wins. And\nthe theme will be...Hinomotoan cuisine.
We're going to settle this with the\nNanakusa flavors that Father taught us.
Have it your way. Whatever proves to you\nthat I'M the one who has what it takes to\nrebuild Nanakusa!
I heard Mitsuba came to have words with\nNazuna, but this is somethin' else.
A battle between sisters with the future\nof Nanakusa hanging in the balance...
(I know I'm in the right. Everything I've\ndone has been to preserve the Nanakusa\nflavor—to protect my family!)
(Efficiency, speed, and quality—\nI've got them all down pat.)
(I'm going to make a next-generation\nrestaurant by leveraging all the skills\nmy father taught me!)
First plate's done.\nGet it to the dining room! Go!
Thank you for your patience!\nThis is a Seven Leaves specialty:\nBroiled Salmon Ogawa.
Wow, talk about fast.\nThat's Seven Leaves for you!
It's not just fast, either. *munch*\nIt's scrumptious, too! This place rocks.
Uh-oh, guys. Nazuna's gettin'\ntens across the board!
(She's got a great mix of ingredients,\nand her plating's top-notch. You\ndefinitely know your stuff, Nazuna.)
(But let's see how she likes THIS!)
Your next course is a Nanakusa specialty:\nShrimp Ankake.
Let me see... *slurp* Ooh, this dashi has\na wonderful umami flavor. It's like the\nvery embodiment of Hinomotoan food!
The seasonal flowers decorating the plate\nare lovely, too. Such attention to detail!
Phew. Glad to see Mitsuba ain't pullin'\nher punches. It's wild that their takes on\nHinomotoan cuisine came out so different.
Yeah. You can really see each chef's\npersonality reflected in their cuisine.
I'm on pins and needles waiting\nto see who will emerge victorious.
(Nazuna, I know well the yearning you feel\nfor Nanakusa.)
(But I'm not going to lose to you.\nYou may have inherited father's\ntechnique, but only I embody his soul!)
(I know you can find it too if you dig deep,\nNazuna. So please...open your eyes!)
All the food's been served.\nThat's the last dish.
All that's left is the moment of truth.
